{"parse":{"title":"International Mother Language Institute","pageid":43711040,"revid":832855649,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption class=\"fn org\">International Mother Language Institute</caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:International_Mother_Language_Institute.JPG\" class=\"image\" title=\"upright=250px\"><img alt=\"upright=250px\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/52/International_Mother_Language_Institute.JPG/220px-International_Mother_Language_Institute.JPG\" width=\"220\" height=\"96\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/52/International_Mother_Language_Institute.JPG/330px-International_Mother_Language_Institute.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/52/International_Mother_Language_Institute.JPG/440px-International_Mother_Language_Institute.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"2300\" data-file-height=\"1000\" /></a><div>International Mother Language Institute in <a href=\"/wiki/Bangladesh\" title=\"Bangladesh\">Bangladesh</a></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Founder(s)</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Government_of_Bangladesh\" title=\"Government of Bangladesh\">Government of Bangladesh</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Established</th><td>\nFebruary 21, 2010</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Mission</th><td>\nPreservation of languages</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Key people</th><td>\nProfessor Jinnat Imtiaz Ali (Director General)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Location</th><td class=\"adr\">\n<span class=\"extended-address\">Segun bagicha, <a href=\"/wiki/Dhaka\" title=\"Dhaka\">Dhaka</a></span>, <span class=\"country-name\"><a href=\"/wiki/Bangladesh\" title=\"Bangladesh\">Bangladesh</a></span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Address</th><td class=\"label\">\n\u200dShaheed captain mansur ali road, 1/Ka, Segun bagicha, Dhaka-1000</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Website</th><td>\n<span class=\"url\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.imli.portal.gov.bd\">www<wbr />.imli<wbr />.portal<wbr />.gov<wbr />.bd</a></span></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>International Mother Language Institute</b> (<b>IMLI</b>) is statutory body in <a href=\"/wiki/Bangladesh\" title=\"Bangladesh\">Bangladesh</a> whose function is the preservation of languages.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Background\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Background</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Structure\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Structure</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=International_Mother_Language_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Declaration of 21 February as the International Mother Language Day by the United Nations on 17 November 1999 is an unprecedented event not only for the Bangla language but also in the history of all mother languages of the world. In a historic meeting commemorating this achievement on 7 December 1999 the honourable Prime Minister of the People\u2019s Republic of Bangladesh Sheikh Hasina announced that an international mother language institute would be established in Dhaka for the research and the preservation of the dignity and the rights  of augmenting/expanding as well as nearly extinct languages of the world. According to that declaration, she laid the foundation of the International Mother Language Institute (IMLI) at 1/ ka Segunbagicha, <a href=\"/wiki/Dhaka\" title=\"Dhaka\">Dhaka</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Bangladesh\" title=\"Bangladesh\">Bangladesh</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>  on 15 March 2001.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> The then Secretary General of the United Nations Kofi A. Annan was present on that occasion. Honourable Prime Minister <a href=\"/wiki/Sheikh_Hasina\" title=\"Sheikh Hasina\">Sheikh Hasina</a> inaugurated the newly constructed building of the International Mother Language Institute on the Martyrs\u2019 Day and International Mother Language Day, 2010. Since then, the International Mother Language Institute is moving ahead with its set mission and vision.\n</p><p>Construction started on April 6, 2003, stopped with the next change of government, and resumed on February 11, 2008. Six stories of the proposed twelve has been built. It was officially completed on February 21, 2010. In 2015 UNESCO applied Category II Institute status to IMLI.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Background\">Background</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=International_Mother_Language_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Background\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"/wiki/Bengali_Language_Movement\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bengali Language Movement\">Bengali language movement</a> of 1952 and <a href=\"/wiki/International_Mother_Language_Day\" title=\"International Mother Language Day\">International Mother Language Day</a> are the main inspiration behind the institute.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Structure\">Structure</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=International_Mother_Language_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Structure\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>There are 40 employees including researchers, officials and employees. Professor Jinnat Imtiaz Ali is the present director general.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=International_Mother_Language_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.thedailystar.net/backpage/protect-all-spoken-words-575971\">\"To protect all spoken words\"</a>. <i>The Daily Star</i>. 2016-02-21<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2016-04-30</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Daily+Star&amp;rft.atitle=To+protect+all+spoken+words&amp;rft.date=2016-02-21&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedailystar.net%2Fbackpage%2Fprotect-all-spoken-words-575971&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInternational+Mother+Language+Institute\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-:0-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-:0_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-:0_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-:0_2-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://en.prothom-alo.com/bangladesh/news/59445/Mother-language-Int.-hardly-functional\">\"Mother Language Institute hardly functional\"</a>. <i>Prothom Alo</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2016-04-30</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Prothom+Alo&amp;rft.atitle=Mother+Language+Institute+hardly+functional&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fen.prothom-alo.com%2Fbangladesh%2Fnews%2F59445%2FMother-language-Int.-hardly-functional&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInternational+Mother+Language+Institute\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.thedailystar.net/news/saving-languages-preserving-knowledge\">\"SAVING LANGUAGES